cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS

The paper deals with low-rank matrix factorization, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.IT (Information Theory) are likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes efficient algorithms for solving the optimization problem, which suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) could be another relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with simulated and real data, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
